{"parse":{"title":"Casing of the Colors","pageid":54507158,"revid":800597724,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:V_Corps_inactivation_ceremony_130612-A-AD638-003.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/29/V_Corps_inactivation_ceremony_130612-A-AD638-003.jpg/220px-V_Corps_inactivation_ceremony_130612-A-AD638-003.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"149\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/29/V_Corps_inactivation_ceremony_130612-A-AD638-003.jpg/330px-V_Corps_inactivation_ceremony_130612-A-AD638-003.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/29/V_Corps_inactivation_ceremony_130612-A-AD638-003.jpg/440px-V_Corps_inactivation_ceremony_130612-A-AD638-003.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4448\" data-file-height=\"3020\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:V_Corps_inactivation_ceremony_130612-A-AD638-003.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>V Corps casing their colors in 2013</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:HMLA-467_deactivation_ceremony.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/11/HMLA-467_deactivation_ceremony.jpg/220px-HMLA-467_deactivation_ceremony.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"147\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/11/HMLA-467_deactivation_ceremony.jpg/330px-HMLA-467_deactivation_ceremony.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/11/HMLA-467_deactivation_ceremony.jpg/440px-HMLA-467_deactivation_ceremony.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"5397\" data-file-height=\"3598\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:HMLA-467_deactivation_ceremony.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Marine Light Attack Helicopter Squadron 467 casing colors in June 2016</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:1st_Cavalry_Division_Color_Casing_Ceremony_DVIDS136678.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e5/1st_Cavalry_Division_Color_Casing_Ceremony_DVIDS136678.jpg/220px-1st_Cavalry_Division_Color_Casing_Ceremony_DVIDS136678.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"128\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e5/1st_Cavalry_Division_Color_Casing_Ceremony_DVIDS136678.jpg/330px-1st_Cavalry_Division_Color_Casing_Ceremony_DVIDS136678.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e5/1st_Cavalry_Division_Color_Casing_Ceremony_DVIDS136678.jpg/440px-1st_Cavalry_Division_Color_Casing_Ceremony_DVIDS136678.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2058\" data-file-height=\"1200\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:1st_Cavalry_Division_Color_Casing_Ceremony_DVIDS136678.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ceremonial charge by 1st Cavalry Division as part of their casing of colors in 2008</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Casing of the Colors</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Military_tradition\" title=\"Military tradition\">traditional</a> ceremony held by <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Army\" title=\"United States Army\">United States Army</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Command_(military_formation)\" title=\"Command (military formation)\">commands</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Brigade#United_States\" title=\"Brigade\">brigades</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Regiment#United_States_Army\" title=\"Regiment\">regiments</a> as well as <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Marine_Corps\" title=\"United States Marine Corps\">United States Marine Corps</a> units. Each of these units have unique flags referred to as \"<a href=\"/wiki/Military_colours,_standards_and_guidons#United_States_Army\" title=\"Military colours, standards and guidons\">colors</a>\" which are carried by the <a href=\"/wiki/Colour_guard#United_States\" title=\"Colour guard\">color guards</a> to represent the unit at military ceremonies. \n</p><p>If a unit is deactivated, the \"Casing of the Colors\" ceremony is held to commemorate the unit and its history which is read aloud to the <a href=\"/wiki/Military_organization#Formation\" title=\"Military organization\">formation</a>. Afterwards, the command's <a href=\"/wiki/Sergeant_major#United_States_Army\" title=\"Sergeant major\">sergeant major</a> then takes the colors from the <a href=\"/wiki/Standard-bearer\" title=\"Standard-bearer\">color bearer</a>'s sling, the deactivation order is read and the colors are presented to the unit commander. The unit commander and the sergeant major then proceed to lower and rotate the colors while furling them into a protective sheath thereby casing the colors. The cased colors are presented to the unit's color bearer who then carries them from the field officially ending the unit command. Cased colors for US Army units are then sent to the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Army_Center_of_Military_History\" title=\"United States Army Center of Military History\">United States Army Center of Military History</a> in Washington, DC.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Casing_of_the_Colors&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.usarmyband.com/pdf/FM_3_21_5.pdf\">Drill and Ceremonies</a></i> Field Manual, Headquarters, Department of the Army, 2006. FM 3-21.5. Section 15-6, on pages 15-4 to 15-6 lists current ceremony in detail.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Casing_of_the_Colors&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Change_of_command\" title=\"Change of command\">Change of command</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Guidon_(United_States)#Army\" title=\"Guidon (United States)\">Guidon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Trooping_the_Colour\" title=\"Trooping the Colour\">Trooping the Colour</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1253\nCached time: 20180901003637\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.012 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.022 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 20/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:54507158-0!canonical and timestamp 20180901003637 and revision id 800597724\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"Ceremonies"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Heraldry_of_the_United_States_military"},{"sortkey":"","*":"United_States_Army_traditions"}],"links":[{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Brigade"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Change of command"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Colour guard"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Command (military formation)"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Guidon (United States)"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Military colours, standards and guidons"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Military organization"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Military tradition"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Regiment"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Serg